			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This has become more important because the new Chrome-IPC-based PPAPI proxy uses a mutexes a lot more than the old SRPC-based PPAPI proxy.  Since the IRT is linked with newlib, we need to improve the performance of NaCl's newlib-based libpthread.

My plan is to reuse nacl-glibc's futex_emulation.c for newlib.  We might add a futex syscall later, but that is less of a priority.

My initial prototype is here:  http://codereview.chromium.org/11358046/
